{
    "name": "Harrow Reader",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Harrow Reader",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 228
                }
            ],
            "html": "A harrow deck is a set of 54 cards with symbolic illustrations that serves as a sacred divining tool. Feared by the superstitious and avoided by those who know better than to tempt fate, harrow readers live and work in traveling communities, often moving from town to town as opportunities arise. For encounters involving social interaction, the harrow reader is a 3rd-level challenge."
        },
        {
            "name": "Mystics",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Dark Rituals",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 228
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Most rituals have a simple gp cost and skills. But what if a desperate NPC is willing to offer something darker, such as lives, souls, or worse? Such a nefarious ritual uses a normal ritual as a baseline, but the DCs and proficiency requirements might be reduced or waived entirely, as might any gp cost."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Forms Of Fortune-Telling",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 228
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": ""
                },
                {
                    "name": "Anthomancy",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 228
                        }
                    ],
                    "html": ": Flowers. <br/><b>Astrology</b>: The cosmic caravan. <br/><b>Demonomancy</b>: Asking demons. <br/><b>Harrowing</b>: Harrow card readings. <br/><b>Haruspicy</b>: Entrails. <br/><b>Ichthyomancy</b>: The next fish caught. <br/><b>Mazomancy</b>: A nursing babe. <br/><b>Oneiromancy</b>: Dreams. <br/><b>Tyromancy</b>: Coagulation of cheese."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mystic Cadres",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 228
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Golarion has several mystic groups. <b>The Church of Razmir</b> offers a plan of 31 steps to divinity. The <b>Esoteric Order of the Palatine Eye</b> seeks celestial truths said to be granted by an ancient angel. <b>Knights of the Aeon Star</b> search for secret lore. Followers of <b>Rivethun</b>, dwarven animism, reach out to spirits to gain knowledge and earn favors."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mystic Rituals",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 228
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "html": "The following are rituals sometimes cast by mystic groups. Those from the <i>Bestiary</i> are available only to appropriate celestials and fiends within the organizations. <ul> <li><a aonid=\"21\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">Abyssal pact</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"22\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">angelic messenger</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">call spirit</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"6\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">commune</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"23\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">Infernal pact</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"15\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">legend lore</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"16\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">planar ally</a></li> <li><a aonid=\"17\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">planar binding</a></li> </ul>"
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 228
                }
            ],
            "html": "Those initiated into the hidden truths and forbidden secrets of the world are forever transformed\u2014or so they claim. To the cynical, a mystic is nothing more than a charlatan or zealot. Others profess to sense an aura around such luminaries and treat them with reverence, lest they offend some harbinger of unspeakable doom."
        }
    ],
